narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A fairly fast-paced introduction to reading Homer, which is significantly more difficult than the Attic texts from L3. I would recommend it to someone who is fairly comfortable reading a page or two of Plato a night. Homer is definitely enjoyable, though the grammar and forms can seem a little random. Professor LeVen is great. Definitely more work than L1-L3, but still very manageable.

Intro to Homer is an introduction to the style of Homer by reading selections of the Odyssey. The learning curve can be a bit steep at first  Homer's Greek is weird  but it's definitely worth it to interact without the complexities of translation with one of the oldest texts humanity has produced.
Course is absolutely recommended---if you're truly prepared for it and know what you're getting into.
Good class. You read some Homer. Not much more difficult than L3
